<br>
I'm sure you learned your lesson out of this Donjira, dont ever explore without consulting a spoiler site.  I used to go everywhere in the dark but now I have maps all over my desk and know exactly where most traps are (except for falling in the jail in Najena like 5 times, good thing the door is bugged so I could get out and find a key for later.)  It's not very Rp'ish, but hey, I'm sure you understand the feeling of losing your corpse and not knowing what to do, but I guess Verant doesn't promote exploration to those who aren't rich or in a large guild.<br>
<br>
Props to those who helped, you're some good people. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uevangelinanife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evangelina Nife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 424<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/2/02 8:50:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=884.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/allencraig1/Syll4.jpg width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My most humble and grateful thanks.</span><hr size=1> If Verant made a pen &amp; paper RPG, it would probably look like this...<br>
