<br>
What happens if this happens?  I don't think you can zone while linkdead, but if you log back in and find yourself in mid air directly over the Hole, the end result is going to be the same anyway.  Or does it end up teleporting you to the zone's default coordinates?<br>
<br>
Anyhow, though I respect what the Hole brings to the history fo Paineel and all, I think it's a little crazy putting a deathtrap of that magnitude in a newbie starting city.  Hold the key a little too long, or expect your Levitate spell to function normally as you explore the area about the Hole, and you're dead.  Not only are you dead, but you're dead at the feet of a nasty NPC in the middle of a high level dungeon with living and unliving creatures.  Recovering your corpse likely involves enlisting the aid of a high level necromancer... a problem particularly on this server with alignment restrictions... though you can get around those if you're willing to abuse a bug.  To me, that's a penalty that's just a little too steep for making a simple misstep.  There's nothing about the history and relationship between the Hole and Paineel that would have prevented the design from being a little more forgiving. <p><FONT FACE="Comic Sans MS">--Tukka</FONT><BR>
