Crink (Rallos Zek)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwyntercrystalbow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wynter Crystalbow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/3/02 12:39:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=884.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Trouble in 'The Hole'. Have some advice?</span><hr size=1> Still, I'm glad your story had a happy ending, Donjira.  If you had fallen in a week or so later I would have been able to help you out since the same thing happened to a member of our brother guild and I logged onto a friend's character (Mage of Brell) snuck in and grabbed his body.  It does work, ladies and gents.  My friend was so intrigued by it he made me teach him how I did it, now he's willing to pull anyone out of the Hole.  Hopefully it doesn't happen anytime soon, but I suppose if you need out, look for Animusumbrae in game and he'll probably help you out.  He's a crazy oddball, since I had nervous fits after my run-in with the undead down there *giggle*  At any rate if anyone else falls into the Hole, look for him (or me I suppose since I know how it's done as well) and we'll get you out as soon as we can.  Very intriguing.  I don't mind the death trap part of it too much, but putting a death trap you can't get your body out of because the zone is Level 45+ is a completely different story. <p>Qilae Aiae'Azhu Kickingwolf - Circle of Sisters<BR>
